PROJECT: Real-time Chat Application with Authentication and File Sharing
============================================================

OVERVIEW
----------------------------------------
The Real-time Chat Application with Authentication and File Sharing is a web-based application that allows users to chat with each other in real-time, share files, and authenticate using Google OAuth. The application is built using Node.js, Express, and MongoDB, and utilizes WebSockets for real-time communication. The application has a client-side UI built using React, and uses various libraries and frameworks to provide a seamless user experience.

COMPONENTS
----------------------------------------
  • server.js  [Entry Point]
    The main entry point of the application, responsible for setting up the Express server and routing.

  • db.js  [Database Configuration]
    The database configuration file, responsible for connecting to the MongoDB database using Mongoose.

  • authRoute.js  [Authentication Route Handler]
    The authentication route handler, responsible for handling authentication-related requests.

  • chatRoute.js  [Chat Route Handler]
    The chat route handler, responsible for handling chat-related requests.

  • messageRoute.js  [Message Route Handler]
    The message route handler, responsible for handling message-related requests.

  • userRoute.js  [User Route Handler]
    The user route handler, responsible for handling user-related requests.

  • authController.js  [Authentication Controller]
    The authentication controller, responsible for handling authentication-related logic.

  • chatController.js  [Chat Controller]
    The chat controller, responsible for handling chat-related logic.

  • messageController.js  [Message Controller]
    The message controller, responsible for handling message-related logic.

  • userController.js  [User Controller]
    The user controller, responsible for handling user-related logic.

ARCHITECTURE PATTERN
----------------------------------------
The application follows a Microservices Architecture pattern, with each component responsible for a specific functionality. The application uses a combination of RESTful APIs and WebSockets to communicate between components. The client-side UI is built using a Model-View-Controller (MVC) pattern, with React components managing the UI and state. The application uses a MongoDB database to store data, and Mongoose to interact with the database. The application also uses various libraries and frameworks, such as Express, Socket.IO, and Passport.js, to provide a seamless user experience.